Mixing.Description: TEOS was stirred into PA66 mixture with a magnetic stirrer in an atmosphere with about 80% relative humidity

ChooseParameter.Other: The solutions in beakers were covered with polyethylene films
Subsequently the solutions stood at rt for 12 h to allow hydrolysis and condensation reactions to continue

Drying-Evaporation.Description: Mixture was poured onto thoroughly cleaned glass plates and dried at rt in a fume hood.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Equipment: DMA 2980 dynamic mechanical analyzer of TA Instruments-Waters LLC, USA

Differential_Scanning_Calorimetry.Equipment: DSC model Q 100 of TA InstrumentsWaters LLC, USA

Atomic_Force_Microscopy.Equipment: VeecoDigital Instruments Multimode SPM (scanning probe microscopy)
Atomic_Force_Microscopy.Description: equipped with Nanoscope IIIa with tapping mode (model RTESP) probes

OpticalMicroscopy.Description: Used for transmittance measurement of the films
